**Category:** essay-draft Frei biblical-hermeneutics narrative Ricoeur Augustinians Aristotelianism

**Abstract:**
Essay dated May 26, 1993, titled "Applying Frei: Another Attempt." The document critiques Frei's systematic separation of religious from narrative biblical reading, arguing that one cannot read the Bible narratively without reading it either religiously or non-religiously. It proposes that the pre-Aristotelian (Augustinian) reading of the Bible corresponds to Frei's pre-Enlightenment mode, while the Aristotelian reading made possible the Enlightenment's scientialis reading. The author aims to render intelligible the Augustinians' resistance to Aristotelianism by reinterpreting their objections and distinguishing modus scientialis from modus narrativus.

**AI Recommendation:** Important theoretical essay applying and critiquing Frei's analysis; develops distinction between scientific and narrative modes of reading.

